ced to ashes by it. Any other form of existence will be yet another dull book in the library of life.\n\n- Charles\n|\nStaying away from news channels, print, and social media makes one realize, that the world actually is a beautiful place to live.\n\n- Kunal\n|\nIntelligence is not knowledge, but it is a state of mind.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nIf you say that you never lie in life,you honestly insult my intelligence.\n\n- Toba Beta, Master of Stupidity\n|\nWords do not express thoughts very well. They always become a little different immediately after they are expressed, a little distorted, a little foolish.\n\n- Hermann\n|\nMost people on earth are just spending time at work, in school or in church without having anything of value to show for it.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nThe Universe doesn't like secrets. It conspires to reveal the truth, to lead you to it.\n\n- Lisa Unger, Beautiful Lies\n|\nYou can only write what you know if you've lived, otherwise, you'll just be writing words.\n\n- Joseph\n|\nThat's chess!' snapped Ron. 'You've got to make some sacrifices!\n\n- J.K. Rowling, Harry Potter and the Sorcerer's Stone\n|\nIf you have committed all things to impacting a life at a time, or impacting a community or society, then welcome to a life of significance.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, The Mountain of Ignorance\n|\nIf we would enter God's reality, all the unknown things would become logical.\n\n- Alin\n|\nAs always, she was carrying the washing. Rudy was carrying two buckets of cold water, or as he put it, two buckets of future ice.\n\n- Markus Zusak, The Book Thief\n|\nGod have pity on the smell of gasolinewhich finds its way like an armthrough a car window,more human than kerosene,more unctuous, more manly.\n\n- S. Jane Sloat, In the Voice of a Minor Saint\n|\nWhoever desire to learn, shall delight in reading.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nWe always think that we are right and we are best, 